			<div class="gallerytext">
<div style="text-align:left;"><b><a href="/wiki/Alvin_Goldman" title="Alvin Goldman">Alvin Ira Goldman</a></b> (born 1938) is an American philosopher who is Board of Governors Professor of <a href="/wiki/Philosophy" title="Philosophy">Philosophy</a> and <a href="/wiki/Cognitive_Science" class="mw-redirect" title="Cognitive Science">Cognitive Science</a> at <a href="/wiki/Rutgers_University" title="Rutgers University">Rutgers University</a> in <a href="/wiki/New_Jersey" title="New Jersey">New Jersey</a> and a leading figure in <a href="/wiki/Epistemology" title="Epistemology">epistemology</a>. <b><a href="/wiki/Alvin_Goldman" title="Alvin Goldman">Read more...</a></b></div>
