			<div class="gallerytext">
<div style="text-align:left;"><div class="thumb tright"><div class="thumbinner" style="width:222px;"><a href="/wiki/File:Kevin_Warwick_2011.jpg" class="image"><img alt="" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/45/Kevin_Warwick_2011.jpg/220px-Kevin_Warwick_2011.jpg" decoding="async" width="220" height="262" class="thumbimage" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/45/Kevin_Warwick_2011.jpg/330px-Kevin_Warwick_2011.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/45/Kevin_Warwick_2011.jpg/440px-Kevin_Warwick_2011.jpg 2x" data-file-width="2854" data-file-height="3403" /></a>  <div class="thumbcaption"><div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:Kevin_Warwick_2011.jpg" class="internal" title="Enlarge"></a></div>Kevin Warwick in 2011</div></div></div><br /><b><a href="/wiki/Kevin_Warwick" title="Kevin Warwick">Kevin Warwick</a></b>  <a href="/wiki/Institution_of_Engineering_and_Technology" title="Institution of Engineering and Technology">FIET</a>, <a href="/wiki/City_and_Guilds_of_London_Institute" title="City and Guilds of London Institute">FCGI</a>, (born 9 February 1954) is a British engineer and Deputy Vice-Chancellor (Research) at <a href="/wiki/Coventry_University" title="Coventry University">Coventry University</a> in the United Kingdom. He is known for his studies on <a href="/wiki/Direct_neural_interface" class="mw-redirect" title="Direct neural interface">direct interfaces</a> between computer systems and the human <a href="/wiki/Nervous_system" title="Nervous system">nervous system</a>, and has also done research concerning <a href="/wiki/Robotics" title="Robotics">robotics</a>. <b><a href="/wiki/Kevin_Warwick" title="Kevin Warwick">Read more...</a></b></div>
